I can only do it on weekends...no fried food during the week :( I'll write a better review once I've had a second try and i'll be able to tell you how I really feel. P.S. my waitress was great...I hope I get her again.

My friend has been telling me about this place for awhile now. I finally got the chance to go and was so glad I did! 

The food was fantastic and so was the service. I asked my server, Eboni, surprise me with her recommended dish, she hit it out of the park with the Southwest Style Chicken. It had amazing flavor and my friend had the Philly Cheesesteak, which was also delicious. 

The atmosphere was neat and there are more than enough screens to keep you up on games. Def try it out. Eboni was our server, and did a great job! Thank you all for a great experience!!! I'll def be back!!

We went here for the cheesiness factor, and because we heard this was the "foody" version of all the "breastaurants," and because it was conveniently located. Cheesy: Check! For foodies: Absolutely not. I wasn't expecting some extensive menu, but likewise wasn't expecting such a limited selection of food items. I settled on the pulled pork sliders, which were "okay," although a bit bland. The atmosphere was as expected: pretty tacky, with lots of blue-collar type men sitting around the bar probably operating under the delusion that the scantily clad women working there were even remotely interested in them. 

A two star experience, but I'm giving it 3 anyway because I'm feeling generous and because it's relatively new.

Stopped by for lunch with a buddy.  Decent food, friendly staff and huge beer selection.  Jennifer was our server and she was awesome!  The place was packed for a Friday lunch.  We both ordered burgers and were satisfied with them.  The fries were heavily seasoned... maybe a bit too much but I ate them.  I will be back.  There were several items on the menu that looked great!  Oh! The interior of the place is really cool.  I don't think they changed much from the previous place.

The restaurant was clean and food was pretty delicious  but the service struggled quite a bit. We waited about 15-20 minutes from our initial greeting before placing our order which included an appetizer. Our drinks were delivered to another table. The mozzarella bites were good! My blt and tomato soup were delicious.  My husband said his burger was ok.  We asked for a to-go box and server cleared away a plate with 3 chicken tenders on it that we had intended to box. However, our server was friendly. We chalked the disappointing service up to being a new restaurant -- they are probably still working out the kinks and getting everyone trained. We will probably go back another time.

Pros: Decor, Alcohol variety, Simple menu selections, TV placement for sports viewing, friendliness of the staff and of course the "scenic views."

Cons: Restrictions on glass size for beer selections with higher ABV% (If you're not driving, then your glass size shouldn't matter), the drive in and out of the parking lot is riddled with potholes, menu items are overpriced for food has is only average in quality. 

The other guests in my party felt that their food was about average, but overpriced for what amounts to being nothing more than your typical bar food. I ordered the Ghost Pepper wings after being informed by the waitress that they were "really hot," but they were nothing of the sort. The wings were small, dry,  overcooked and the heat level of the sauce was very disappointing. Their Ghost Pepper wings had about the same heat level as what you might expect from the "hot" selection on a menu at BW3. 

Overall, the environment was aesthetically pleasing and the staff were very courteous, but the food was nothing to rave about. I have to agree with the guests in my party: The food quality is what you might expect to find in any pub, only more expensive. I may return for a beer and a basket of their fire fries, but certainly not for a meal.

Had the fish tacos average at best
Just so so
Girlie bar girls but with bad waitress skills

Kelcie is a horrible bartender.  We waited to order food for over 10 minutes.  Food was good , not worth the bad service though.  Beer sucks at 27.8 degrees, too icy.  Took over fifteen minutes to pay the bill and it wasn't even busy.

As a kid we would occasionally eat at places like Rainforest Cafe & Planet Hollywood. It was all about the atmosphere. It seems like Twin Peaks serves the market with a similar approach. The food is fine. Drinks are fine. The service completely varies with each visit -- it seems best when sitting at the bar, less than mediocre at a table. However, it is probably one of the best places in the area to watch multiple games at once. So I guess at this age I'm willing to trade a great dining experience for something more mediocre if it means abundant viewing options on a Sunday during football season. 

Side note: Can anyone explain to me why every stall in the women's restroom has a 3 inch gap on both sides of the door? All these years...and it hasn't stopped being weird.

My husband, myself and our friends have always wanted to try Twin Peaks and drove 45 minutes to do so and it was a complete let down. Our friends arrived before us and were already seated. When we walked in, there were 5 girls standing in the front and not one of them greeted us or asked if they could help us. None of the 5 girls said one word to us. There were no other guests either. So we just decided to find our friends on our own. 

Once we were all seated, it took 15 minutes for our waitress to even ask us what we wanted to drink. Mind you, this place was not busy at all. We orderd the 4 shot deal, and the shots tasted watered down. The fried pickles were great. The rest of the food was below average in all of our opinions. And then, our waitress messed up our tickets. 

The biggest let down was the customer service and with everything combined, it was a bad experience and the ONLY reason it's getting two stars is because of the fried pickles. We will not be back.
There was a horrible 45 minute wait on our food to be done. So we didn't get to eat, paid for our drinks and had a couple shots. Left with a $15 bill and disappointment.
The food was awful. I had chili and a burger. The service was nothing special. I felt like we paid $40 for a crappy lunch because of some boobies.
Party of 8 sat for 15 minutes after ordering drinks before leaving. Didn't want to wait for dinner. Worst service ever.

Here is the breakdown on my rating. 4 stars for the food, great flavors and fresh home style cooking. I have only had one misstep when I tried to customize a salad and so maybe I was being too difficult. I give 4 stars to the staff, for the most part they are friendly and provide great service. 1 star to the management, they make odd choices like charging guest who are in the restaurant a cover charge because of some stupid MMA fight. 1 star for the customers, actually most people who go here are nice, upstanding, professionals. The small minority that do not know how to dress and act in public ruin the atmosphere. Averages out to 3 stars.

Food is good. Service is piss poor. There are a lot of TVs, but it takes an act of congress to get it on the game you want to see and there is no guarantee that it will stay on your game until the end. Tonight, the IU basketball game was switched with 2:30 to go (tied) for a MMA bout. Meanwhile, there was the same NBA game on 2 TVs next to each other at the bar.  Whoever is running this needs a course in common sense. I don't think I'll be back. There are too many other options.

I ordered the hangover and no where on the menu does it say anything about onion I got the sandwich and it was full of onions I'm highly allergic that's something you might want to put on your menu for people that have food allergies..

Food is great ... But the service sucks. The girls that work there have horrible attitudes Ive been there about 4 times and each time same horrible attitudes. Its safe to say I will not be going here again

Recently went to this location and I have mixed reviews. Food and booze came out quick and was good. It's the service is where my issue is. 
Server took my order, but very quickly gave me the bill. Felt like they were trying to rush me out. Look I get it, spent years in restaurant business. But don't throw me the bill unless I ask for it, makes people feel like they are not allowed to order more. Especially when they don't even acknowledge that you are there after. Gave the server $20 on a &45 dollar bill. You would think they would try and get more out of me at that point!! But no, did not speak to me once after I paid. 
I understand that this place has a theme, and that's mainly what people go for. But that only gets you so far. I have gone through the reviews of this location and others. And I have not seen management even try and apologize once at this location, once!!Where as at the other one I looked at. First review I read management had responded. 
Enjoyed the food and booze and willing to give it another shot. But if service does not prove to be nothing more then girls showing off the boobs and ass, and relying on just that to make money, I will not come back nor recommend this specific location to anyone.

First off overall a good place to come. As we arrived, no one greeted us and took a minute too long to seat us when there was no wait and plenty of room. The service was average (girl forgot what sample of beer was what) my steak was ordered medium rare and came out medium. Didn't ruin the meal as it was still good. The mashed potatoes are amazing as well as the mac and cheese, highly recommended. My boyfriend got the "Hangover Burger" it was very good! The fries are also great and have a nice seasoning. Great place to watch sports and has a very unique environment. I think their downfall is a bunch of young inexperienced girls trying to run the place. Very good price though!
Took me ten minutes to order a beer from the waitresses fixated on their phones.  Beer was good service wasn't what I was expecting

I had high hopes for this place. We heard they have great food. My husband and I went in during slower hours on a Friday. LOTS of empty tables so we thought it shouldn't be too long of a wait with our waitress. She took a while to get our drinks.  We ordered our food. He got the pot roast, I got the steak salad and added shrimp. Their menu is very small, not much to choose from. Like I said, it was not busy. It took almost an hour to get our food and it was cooked fine but it was so salty I couldn't eat it. Even my husband, who pours salt on everything, said it was so salty he didn't have to put salt on there. Which is ok for him but for normal people it was too much. 
On a side note, I personally have no problem with how the staff is dressed, or I wouldn't have went in, but is it mandatory to hire only anorexic looking females? These girls really do not look healthy. Out of the 10+ servers only 2 seemed to weigh over 110 lbs. The girls were extremely pleasant and nice though but the service was not that great either.

Service was not very good. Asked for water did not receive it. Ask for mayonnaise extra and did not receive it. The music was so loud that the waitress did not hear our order. She kept asking over and over what we had selected. there was no choice between regular fries and fire fries. No ketchup was offered at the table. The menu selections are very limited. But they do have a large beer and liquor selection. observing the other waiters and waitresses, they did not seem to be in a hurry to do anything one way or the other. The hamburger that I had, was just like any other hamburger at any other restaurant. Nothing exceptional.it seems to be a very disorganized restaurant and management staff. In fact, I saw no management in the restaurant at all. More training is needed definitely. it is nice though to have a very large flatscreen TVs to watch all the available games and sports on.

This was our 3rd time eating here. We have had a bad experience each time. This time the waitress was absolutely clueless and rude. It was Saturday and it should have been a kids eat free day. We explained that to the waitress and she looked at us like we were idiots. She then came back and the kids drinks were still on the bill. We asked for those to be taken off and she huffed and puffed and gave more attitude. My wife got the Hangover burger and it was as thin as a Mcdonalds cheeseburger and the egg was completely cooked not sunnyside up. I got the chicken strip basket and my 2 boys hot the kids chicken strips. The strips are somewhat slimy. The aren't very crispy at all. I will say the fries are very good and the beer is cold! 
I won't be coming back for a meal but I might come back to sit at the bar and watch a game. Hopefully the service will get better over time.
Excellent menu items and great selection of beers. Good place for sporting events via tv with plenty of seating and good service. Try the chili loaded it's excellent.

Decided to check out Twin Peaks after finding my favorite Indian Restaurant closed at 3:00. (I know, I should know this) My date and I decided to go for the sampler appetizer, the BLT and the Philly steak n cheese. The appetizer was really good consisting of pickle chips, boneless buffalo wings, and mozzarella cubes. The pickle chips were pretty tasty. The buffalo wings were the norm and the mozzarella cubes were okay. Nothing to write home about. My BLT was nicely prepared but I didn't care for the spicy bacon (may have been pepper bacon) and the lack of mayo. The sourdough  bread it was served on was really good. My date didn't care for the Philly steak n cheese. He said the bread wasn't very good. He said Penn Station is better. The fire fried that come with the sandwiches are thicker cute and pretty good.

I will give them another shot to try the pot roast but if it isn't good I probably won't go here again. 

One nice perk is the decor. It's the old Loon Lake Lodge so the rustic feel is still there and the fireplace is a nice touch.

I've been to this location several times. Every time I go the service is fast & friendly. The beer is always ice cold and the food always comes out hot. The girls are friendly, which is nice. The girls also don't just pay attention to the man you're with, so that's a plus.

I'll be honest, it's alright but not great. Typical bar restaurant akin to an R-rated Applebee's. We're glad we tried it, but I doubt we'll be making a return visit.

Whiskey selection was surprisingly large, but as a beer guy, I was left kinda disappointed. Fat Tire is as exotic as it gets.

Got the pablano chicken and the lady got the fish tacos. We both decided they were "meh". If I'm going to go ogle women and drink cheap beer, I'll stick to Hooters Wings.

Sweet bear statue though.

I tried Twin Peaks for 1st time today and likely my last. It wasn't busy at 4:00 and I was greeted, seated and waited on very quickly. Since I was working I had iced tea so can't comment on beer selection. I have no complaints with service or server. Elizabeth was friendly and efficient. Very limited menu though. A handful of appetizers, about half dozen burgers a couple of chicken sandwiches and fish tacos. Also a few "dinner" type offerings. I'm not necessarily a healthy type eater but if you are you'll go hungry here. I ordered the chicken ranch. It was very sloppy so watch out shirt front and way over seasoned. It had so much pepper on it I'm afraid I'm going to regret it tomorrow morning. Same way with the fire fries, way too much salty cajun seasoning on frozen steak cut fries. All in all they're just meh. 4 stars though for waitress objectifying, I feel like I have to leave a bigger tip...is there a term for this? I'll have to call A Way With Words.

Nothing special about this place. Mediocre food with decent service. Waitresses know nothing about the food on the menu, so don't bother asking. This is definitely only here to entertain lonely men. If you want good food, there are plenty of better options nearby.

First time trying the Twin Peaks breastaurant. Wife and I found the place after lunch time, after most of the Bros had checked out, so the place was pretty laid back. Toni was polite, and took care of us like a good host should, and looked great to boot. Beers were ice cold (great for this obnoxiously hot and humid summer!) and the selection covered a lot of beer types. Wings were pretty good, better than B-Dubs for sure. French fries on the side were kinda bland; they should just invest in a fry slicer and make them fresh, it isn't hard to do. Plenty of TVs everywhere to catch just about every sport you could want to watch. Would go back next time we're in Indy.

I'm have a Twin Peaks. It's my cuz per   Bachelor party.   The  Waitress at twin peaks (Tyler Walker) is the best and she is a very good waitress. Plus Tyler works hard at all  her tables. Just want the thanks Twin  peaks and Tyler Walker for a very good time.

Twin peaks has been open for a couple of months and I had heard good things about the food and the scenery and decided to check it out. I was told by some of my friends that it was substantially better than Hooters in both regards as well. 

We were seated faster than I expected and initially thought it was strange that we were sitting at a very long table along with others. The table was separated by a piece of wood with an ax in it. It actually worked pretty well. 

Our waitress, Alyssa, was very friendly and brought us our beer pretty quick. It was the coldest beer I have ever had and it was served in a FROZEN glass not just frosted. The surface of the beer froze in about a minute. The beer was certainly a great experience.

Alyssa and the other waitresses were wearing tight tan shorts with red "shirtinis" (a word I just made up to mean a bikini top that has just a little more fabric to make it look like a shirt). They were for and friendly. 

The food was a mixed bag. I had the cheese bites as an appetizer. They were fantastic. My only complaint was that there weren't enough of them. My meal was  was the bbq bacon burger and fries. The fries were pretty good. They are a steak fry with a season salt. I would have liked more seasoning but my fiancé wanted less. The burger is the problem. It had great presentation and the bacon was done well but when I started getting into the burger, it fell flat on flavor. There was very little sauce and the meat didn't have a full grilled taste. I would expect a burger and fries that cost $9 would be grilled and it was obvious that It came off of a flat grill. 

The menu was also very small. I will go back but not so much for the burgers.
Seriously the shitest Indiana service. I only come because it closes late and its food is good. But their waitresses are trash

Food was pretty good, I had the chipotle chicken and it had a nice kick. Chips and queso were good, we wanted the pulled pork nachos, but they were sold out. Not much of a wine selection, but the beer was apparently very cold. Our server was really bad. She was very friendly, but did not seem to grasp our order. She forgot a lot and did not even ask for any food order until we had been there 30 minutes. She may have been new to serving.

Attentive service and woodsy decor sets this restaurant apart from the competition. Booths with TV's make watching the game an intimate experience. Menu is limited but the cuisine is stellar. The only thing preventing this place from 5 stars is the lack of a vegetarian entrée.

This place is called "Twin Peaks" which, like "Hooters", is a not so subtle way of reminding you why you really came here. You didn't come here for gourmet food. You didn't come here to discuss Plato and Dostoevsky with PhD students who are working as waitresses to help pay tuition. You came here for the twin peaks.

Having said that, the food is on par with other sports bars, which means it's mediocre. So why four stars instead of the 2-3 stars I consistently give to sports bars with mediocre food (which is all of them)? Because twin peaks.
Good was on par with your typical sports bar. Clearly the cleavage motif is where they concentrate most of their efforts. Great place for game day food.

The wife and I stopped in here on a Saturday afternoon for an early dinner after catching a matinee up on 96th street. The parking lot was about half filled, but it looked like a lot less people inside as the restaurant is HUGE and very open. We were greeted by no less than 6 waitresses/hostesses standing around the hostess station. The person taking us to our table, who ended up being our waitress, decided to finish her conversation she was having with the other girls before seating us. It was kind of annoying, but she was very pleasant otherwise. 

The menu isn't extensive as others have previously mentioned. I decided on the "hangover burger" which is your basic hamburger with the addition of a fried egg on top. It was good but I have to say I prefer the Royal Red Robin over it. The fries served with it were pretty tasty with the seasoning they added to them. My Wife decided to just get the pulled pork nachos appetizer for her meal and we would share them. WOW there was a lot of food on that plate. They were very good, but I was too full to be of much help after my burger and we barely scratched the surface. At one point the waitress came by and said, "I was going to tell you how big they were after you ordered them."......haha ok why didn't you? We took them home and had them the next day. No big deal. 

My favorite part about Twin Peaks, besides the obvious, was how cold the beer was! They are very proud of how cold they keep the beer as there is an indicator on the wall keeping customers informed of just how cold it was. It fluctuated from 27 to 30 degrees while we were there. While there isn't an overabundance of choices, it was super refreshing. The top of the beer had small ice crystals forming it was so cold. DELICIOUS! Especially on a 90 degree day.

I don't think it would be a monthly trip, but we would definitely take friends back for the experience or just drop in for a drink. Like I said, the inside was huge with plenty of TVs everywhere you looked. It would be a great place to take a big group.

Do you want to read the good written material I have created today?

The Indy 500.  While thousands rushed to the track to drown themselves in alcohol in the blazing sun watching race cars zoom across the track going at speeds I've never traveled, I learned in the background.  I made a decision to go in search of a good spot to watch the race on television yesterday and that is a good thing today.  It sent me spiraling to Twin Peaks, a place I had listed on my calendar and scratched off the original day I chose to go.  Still my sub-conscious would not let me forget what I had tried to erase.  It pushed me in that direction and I arrived and met my destiny restoring the balance of today.  I walked in with a quarter.  I ordered a water and sat at the bar.  My bartender was a seasoned veteran.  She'd been there since it opened.  Her next career goal in life is to be a housewife.  I sat there for hours, just learning from the environment and her.  The pack sitting to my left get louder as their drinks keep getting refilled.  One of them speaks up and decides to order shots for the group.  I chime in, can I have one too?  No.  Then he changes his mind, calls it karma, and orders me up one.  Did we just become best friends?  No.  I soon learn what attracts me to the bartender, she reminds me of a person I knew in the past, Heather.  Coincidentally enough, a red head strolls into the bar to work next to my bartender and her name is Heather.  So I spend a few hours there just learning and being in the space.  I'm not a king.  I say at one point to the guy who bought the shots.  Kiss the ring bitch.  His response, drowning himself in booze.  When him and his pack are about to leave, he bows and kisses my hand.  

I return after a visit home for a nap and dinner.  My bartender and Heather are still there, grinding it through on a Sunday race day.  I order a glass a house red and the banana pudding.  Both were good then as of today.  It wasn't about me that good day, it was about her, the bartender, and Heather, and that's a good thing today.

I'm a big sports bar guy and a sports bar food guy and don't expect a sports bar to be 5 star dining. Let me answer a question that people ask me when I said I ate there. "Is it okay to bring your wife and kids there to watch a game?" The servers do wear low cut shirts and shorts, but nothing that was any different than other themed sports bars. When I was there, there were groups of women together and also couples there. There were a few families with children there. 

The food is what made me give it a try....well that and the ridiculously cold beer. 

I am a big fan of nachos....good nachos. Twin peaks has good nachos, very good nachos. they are big enough for 2-3 people and be pretty full. We ate mostly appetizers while we were there. We had the sampler plate which has mozzarella bites, Fried Pickles and Boneless buffalo bites. They were really good. Even with them being fried they were not soggy from grease. Have boneless chicken instead of bone on wings in a sampler was a great surprise and was welcomed with an open mouth. I also had The cup of chili and it was very flavorful and I wish I would have got The bowl of chili instead. The food over all was above average for a sports bar. next time we might move to entrees next time.

For dessert we had the bread pudding and it was really good. I would definitely get it again. My wife are the ice cream and brownie dessert. She would get it again also. I also wanted the apple dessert they had on the menu, but the server says they don't carry it and wishes they would take it off them menu if they don't plan on carrying it.

It is my new favorite sports bar. Almost forgot they have a crazy amount of TVs and they are numbered so you can ask the server to change that tv to a game you would like to watch. They also have tvs over all the urinals in the men's room.
Dirty everywhere. They serve food ?? Really ?? Who gives. Food not Michelin Rated but who cares. Love tight shirts and tops.  Tattoos and bedazzled belts.  So hot. Stripper smell permeates.

My last visit to Twin Peaks, and it will be my last. I was told by the 21 and a half year old bartender that it was against the law to order a beer and a Crown on the rocks. 
I am 56 years old and I know this is an absolute crock of poop!! Order them all the time. Including the last two times I have been to Twin Peaks!!!
Fast forward to two gentleman across the bar. One orders a shot and a beer, the other a special shot and beer. Too surprise I say, "thought that was against the law"?  "They don't have ice in them". Now she begins to tell me how long she's has be a so called bartender,  whatever. Oh the patronizing b$&ch!! 
The service sucks, to busy showing their asses, and giggling to help anyone. 
Now this is at the bar mind you, don't want to talk bad about the whole wait staff just Heather!!

I was looking forward to eating here, my last experience the food and service in Knoxville were great. No so here. The waitress took close to 10 minutes to show up for my drink order. I gave my dinner order at the same time my iced tea showed up quickly but it took awhile for salad. I found out why when the salad and my steak entree showed up together. I sent the steak back and ate the salad that was crisp, fresh and very good. The steak came back out like warm and done to less than medium rare. The vegetables were good but also less than luke warm. I would  not visit this location again.

So gross it's almost like a sex shop shop and eat gross I will never eat here again not that I did but the sign on the highway has got to go sorry sore eyesight for caselton if it's not bad enough I rock on eb on your career needs shut the fuck down it's like a parlor all over again eewwe
Good food . Cold beer . Good conversation . Every time I go to the food taste great . I have not been dissatisfied at all

I stopped in for the first time tonight.  I had the Venison Chili.  It was very good!  Colleen was very friendly and attentive even though she was going on 9+ hours at work.  I'll definitely be coming back with friends!

We've been wanting to try this franchise. Disappointed with the service. Our waitress had no personality and did not want to be there. There'd be long spans of time where she was MIA. I don't know if it was an off night but it seemed like none of the workers were happy to be there. We were there on a Saturday night around 8:30pm. Great beer selection. We tried the sampler and it was very good. Had the pot roast and It was ok. The potatoes were raw and the other veggies seemed to oily.  It's a nice place to watch a game with some appetizers. We were from out of town so I'm hoping the location in our area is better than this location.

I have to say we had a really good experience here.  Honestly, what attracted me to the place is the 29 degrees beer.  I wanted it, and I got it, and I loved it.  I had their brew, the Knotty Brunette.  It's a dark brown beer, but lighter than a lager.  I was surprised at how light tasting it is, and I really like it.  We had the sirloin steak with garlic mashed and broccoli and the bread pudding for dessert.  The steak was prepared properly and not tough, the mashed potatoes had just the right taste of garlic without over powering, and the broccoli was cooked without being wilted to death.  The bread pudding had the texture of almost a cake and had raisins and a nice bourbon sauce topped with ice cream.  Loved how many TV's were in every direction.  The inside space is huge, they have two bars, and the decor is really cute.  While it is true that this is the type of place whose staff are young ladies with low cut tops and high cut shorts, it's not too extreme, and the frosty beer is just worth it.

Very Cold Beer, Great Friendly Service, and good food.  They do not add salt to anything.  I usually sit at the bar and you have to ask for salt as it is not sit out (maybe they are trying to reduce people's salt usage) ... the big negative is they are always changing and removing items from the menu.  They used to have an amazing meatloaf .. no longer removed it from the menu.   Chicken tacos WERE amazing.. grilled chicken with various seasoning diced up and loaded into three tacos.. now you just get two and it is a fried chicken strip.. I would avoid... go with naked or smoked wings... or the Texas style Cheese Steak.. the regular cheese steak is good too

Beautiful women, great service, great food. Had a wonderful experience. Would advice to call and ask if they are having a bikini night as it wouldn't be family friend to this point. They definitely push the sexual agenda to attract business. Too many positive though that out weigh the negative. Enjoy it!

Amazing!!! 
This was my first time here. I felt very comfortable with the girls working there. They were very nice to each other and seemed to have great relationships. Lindsay was the bartender and she was great! Very sweet and very knowledgeable of everything they had to offer. The store was very clean and the staff knew exactly what was expected of them. The bar back assisted the bartender and they had great chemistry.
Good chicken wings, waitresses have a great attitudes went there on a Saturday night, lots of families and good sports, founders all day IPA on tap
Beer was extremely cold, so made it Amazing lol .  Service was super nice and food.. if u get the wings bone in there HUGEEEEE TRY THE JALAPEÑO BUTTER

I enjoy the atmosphere of this place. The bartender, Jessica, was amazing and very nice and seemed interested in conversation. The beer I ordered came out fast and was ice cold. The food was amazing too, no issues with it and was a speedy delivery to me.

Icy cold draft beer and nice service.  I felt a lil creepy at first here as we came on "Lingerie day", or what my people call "Friday ". After a while you settle in and it's just a good, massive sports bar that serves high-end bar food. 
The venison chili was surprisingly good. Nice layers of savory gravy and the perfect meat to beans ratio.  Go off the reservation and order the buck. 
My dining tastes tend to be a lil bipolar, so from there I ordered the meatless Imposter Burger. This was really strange for a veggie burger.  It was really juicy and meaty - almost too wet for me, but you gotta try this one for yourself.
Beer is not better at 27.5 degrees! The servers were clueless! Only 2 sizes for beer- 10oz and 22oz? Don't expect much from Twin Peaks, the 'Peaks' weren't that great.
Excellent service! Wait time for meal was not long. Continually checked on by server. Food was cooked perfectly! Very satisfied.

Parking lot was dead we came right after lunch. Seated right away but took awhile to see the waitress. Sweet Tea had a different taste than normal. Ordered fried pickles they were good. The fish and chips super greasy and the chicken fried chicken was also. Mac and cheese had no flavor. The only good was the waitress was nice.
Had a great time at this restaurant! Dana (Knoxville)was a wonderful server! Keep up the great job!! We loved getting to know you!

My Wife and I stopped in for lunch before heading to a New Year's Eve Party.  The place was pretty dead for lunch, but it was probably going to be busy for the college football playoff games. 

The hostess wasn't that friendly and didn't seem to be happy that we were there.  Always a good start....

There are more BIG TV's than any place I've ever visited.  There are almost too many if that's possible.  It was a little annoying that even though all of the TV's were the same size and model they couldn't sync the color adjustments so it made for uncomfortable viewing.  At least the feed was all in sync timing wise.

Our server was very attentive and friendly  I ordered the fish tacos which were very good and my wife had the meatloaf which she also enjoyed.  I had a few draft beers which were quite cold.  I didn't really like the frosty mugs though.  They had too much frost and I ended up with a lot of ice in all three of the beers I ordered.

The other servers that walked by seemed to be going through the motions and were never smiling.  They really made it kind of an uncomfortable environment.  I think if they would smile a little it would go a long way to making the place more enjoyable.

Overall the place just seems too large and not the kind of place I would like to hang out and watch sports.  If you advertise cold beer why does it have to come in an icy cup.  It kind of ruins the beer when there is that much ice floating in it.

I usually sit at the bar , but today I sat in Alexis section . She is very sweet and never thought twice to accommodate us no matter what we asked ! I will definitely come back for her service and attentiveness
The pulled pork sliders are fabulous. We went on a busy Saturday night, and service in the bar was good.
I thought the food was pretty good, not sure about the subpar reviews I read. Service was pleasant. Screens galore for TNF.

Came to Twin Peaks after seeing undercover boss a while a back and was in the area. We absolutely LOVED it our server Ty she was outstanding. There wasn't a moment we were without anything we needed and she was super friendly! When we got ready to leave we decided we wanted to see if they had shirts and Paul was kind enough to grab us two shirts he had since they don't sell them in store now. The service was above and beyond and we will definitely be making a trip back!

First time at a Twin Peaks and I enjoyed it immensely. Sat at the bar with Mackenzie as our caretaker so to speak. She was awesome and friendly. Had the Hangover burger to help with my current hangover and it hit the spot. Very good experience.

Lousy burgers - barely warmish.  Lettuce and tomato are poor quality, and broccoli is cooked to death.  Patty is pre-made, frozen, and not a good one. French fries are good and hot, at least. 

Don't know if this is indicative of the chain, but so far, no good.
Fun restaurant with good food and friendly service!  I went there for an informal business lunch.  Our waitresses, Emage and Asia, were very accommodating and friendly.

If you like flannel, chopping wood, and wildlife... who am I kidding. If you like looking at their other peaks that they have on display, and they have a bunch, (meaning the ladies working there.) The food is better than Hooters and the prices are better. Love the beer choices, and the beer is always freezing cold. Just be prepared to see a lot of almost half naked chicken wings walking around. Someone needs to feed them chickens. All jokes aside. My husband and myself go here at least once a month.
Tomato soup and BLT was awesome. Beer is ice cold. Great music.. Our waitress could of been better. More of a personality.. Saw others smiling and being courteous

Awesome food...great atmosphere...ok location...but unfortunately  the service gets zero stars.  Horrible service! .Staff doesn't get it...too bad because this place could be awesome!   If you do go, get their bacon appetizer, it is amazing!

It's like Hooters on steroids. They have a good beer selection, decent food, and of course attractive waitresses. I like the giant log cabin feel of this restaurant and it's usually a good place to grab a beer after work if you are wanting to get served quickly.

My family and I went to Twin Peaks for the first time. Not only was the food delicious and exceeded our expectations, the atmosphere and drinks deserve  nothing but 5 stars. Our waitress Mckenzie was so pleasant and tentative, service was great! Manager Emilio checked on us to make sure we were having a great experience. We appreciate this kind of service and will definitely be returning! Great job Twin Peaks!

Come to bar with the porch for all your game day needs. There's a dynamic duo named kelsi and kaylee and their the bomb.com... cheesy but for real, its a good time, in a great atmosphere where they make a Texan feel right at home. If somehow you don't have the best time, hit up Brian. He holds the whole place down. So, i guess you could say the terrific service is an extension of his great management. Come see for yourself.

I had a phenomenal experience at twin peaks this evening. Our server, shayla, was a lot of fun and my burger was delicious. I came in with 9 friends (who can get pretty rowdy) and shayla handled all of us exceptionally. I will definitely be returning!!

The food was actually pretty good here I couldn't believe it. A lot more flavorful than I thought it would be. But it did taste extremely processed. Our service was excellent and the scenery was great as well. But I don't want to come back... but I get why guys go there lol  not mad at yeah

Honestly I was against the advertisement before they opened, j thought it was going to be a strip club.  If they wouldn't have advertised making the place look sleazy they would attract more patrons. I rarely enjoy the food at most restaurants but YUM, the fish tacos are much better than Bonefish and the salsa is warm and absolutely the best in town.   Upscale bar food! Our server Jenna & Christina cute cute cute and their outfits are no worse than you see in any summer day.  Service was excellent.  Not a big deal ladies. Food is awesome!

A great new place in indy with over 40 craft beers on tap.  They also provide a decent menu of typical pub style food with a twist.  The best part obviously is the scenery and friendly customer service. If you are a sports fan there are also plenty of TV's with every channel playing.  Try the "ghost heat" wings... They have a kick!!!

Just left my birthday dinner at Twin Peaks and it was awesome. Alyssa and Bre made us feel like we had been friends forever. Great service and really good food. I had the Philly cheesesteak and it was amazing. The twin peaks sundae was awesome too!  Thanks Bre and Alyssa!
Great food and times.  Surprised with lower reviews.  Awesome cold beer 29 degrees cold!  Solid food.  Section that seats/accommodates larger crowds and great service from Melanie!

Good place. Cold beer.  Service started off slow, but when bartenders were caught up they were friendly and talked ... provided personable service and definitely one of the better Twin Peaks I have been to... next time I will see how they do... bareback was excellent as well.

Micayla was extremely professional , pleasant, a great server. She made our dining experience very nice. She truly cared about our table . Ask for her!
Paul the manager was great
One of the best sports bars we've been too and always go to one if they have one in the town we are in

Not impressed. To start, the group of hostesses at the front were far too busy socializing with each other to bother to acknowledge us. When we were on our way to be seated, we noticed that the restaurant smelled strongly of sewage throughout, luckily we were seated in the back where it wasn't AS FOUL, but still there nonetheless. Frankly, I lost most of my appetite already because of that stench. The hostess sat us down and seemingly forgot about us, as a server didn't come around to get our drink orders for another 20 minutes. They weren't even busy. The server was not friendly and wasn't familiar with the drink or food menus, she didn't want to answer questions that my father had about the menu. Our food came out quickly but was not good. In a party of 6, half of us did not get what we ordered, and the food we received was all either way overcooked, or undercooked. My husband felt that his chicken wings tasted off, and has been sick to his stomach for the last two hours. None of us had been here before tonight and it's really unlikely that we'll be back. Pretty dissatisfied with this place, which was surprising because of all the hype we've heard. I don't get what all the hype was about for unpleasant service, wrong orders, sewage smell, not to mention that everything was so sticky from our table to our silverware and glasses.

Having a great lunch a Twin Peaks today! 
Trying the new Green Chili Chicken soup and a Burger. Great atmosphere at the bar. Samantha and Jessica  take care of your every need. I have become a regular!

We were in town for a baseball tournament.
Most of the team decended in for dinner so our teenage boys could appreciate a meal "with a view".
The servers were attentive and gave the boys some fun.
Food was good for the large chain they are.
Mostly fried foods, very few vegetable options.
Bison is on the menu which is at the very least, a healthier option.
Personally I left with a fun case of food related heartburn but our group had fun.
If you're in the area, with a group or looking for a dinner with "peaks", it's worth trying once.

I normally like to go to this place, but yesterday was horrible. The waitress had zero personality to start with. There were four of us there to drink, eat and watch the football games. We spent quite a lot of money and were there for a couple hours when a manager told us that we were buying too many drinks and there was a family sitting next to us. We had a driver who had 0 beers or alcoholic drinks, and we were not being disrespectful or rude to anyone. I look over at the family and they weren't paying a bit of attention to us. It didn't look like they were bothered at all.

 Then we were accused of turning off tv's and the manager tried to stare us down. I'm sure he got his courage from the policeman who was working the door. Needless to say, we weren't intimidated. It was pretty busy there and I was assuming that the point was to let people watch some games, have a good time, and they make money in the process. I won't be going back there anytime soon.

I enjoy this place because of the size and super cold beer, but the service is the worst. The food is hit or miss depending on the night, as well as the waitresses attitudes. 

If you are a sports fan that likes super cold beer, and don't really mind if the food is great, then this is the place for you.
First time here and didnt know what to expect. Our server was Ty. She was awesome and made our stay exceptional. I will be back to this place when ever i get a chance.

This place would be five stars if it was for the fruit flies at our booth. I am pretty sure a fruit fly problem comes from miss managed liquor bottles at the bar. At least, that is what I have learned from Bar Rescue.

Besides that....The food was awesome. I love wings, and their wings were top notch. I got my wings breaded like I would at Hooters, and their breading is nice and crisp. Their sauces are good although not as many to choose from as Buffalo Wing Wings. In always better than Wings, Etc. I liked their wings above all wings because of the breading. You can get them without breading too.

They have two beers that are made for them. One they claimed was like a Blue Moon, but Blue Moon is better. The other is a brown ale. Both were good. They advertise 29 degree cold beer. I had to be that temperature, because it was slightly slushy at the top. I would rather the beer just be in the high 30's. No need to have ice in me beer.

They have TVs at all the booths from what I could tell. It was really neat to watch a college football game at my table. The restaurant sound system was turned to play that game over the speaker system. On a side note, not all the tables were turned to the same channel. Not sure if you can get it changed for your table or not. 

The ambiance of the place looks like the inside of a log cabin. It has a Ron Swanson vibe from Parks and Recreation. Long tables have axes dividing them. Some chairs are made of of branches. Tables are made of slabs of wood. The walls are decorated with pin up girl calendars and beer related materials. The ladies looked very pretty in their outfits.

I would come here again. Hope they fixed their fruit fly problem. I informed corporate about it hoping it gets fixed.

The beer was cold and good. I had the wings which tasted like grocery store ones. My husband and son had burgers which they said were good. My son said there was way too much mayo on his but other than that. The service I was really not impressed with. We sat with dirty dishes at our table the entire time. Twice she would come over and take maybe two glasses but not come back for rest. There was a shift change and the other waitress same thing. Both were sweet but could of cleared our table as we sat there finishing up our beers.

I have frequented Twin Peaks for nearly four months, but tonight was the best by far. Symone took wonderful care of me, and although Mattice wasn't my server, she made sure to make her way over to thank me for being such a great customer. Ashley is a manager, but she genuinely spends time with every customer assuring every need is met. I wouldn't recommend any other place before this one!
Do yourself a favor and only come here for a cold beer & watch sports. The food is bland, cold and all around unappealing to the eyes. I do believe they have the coldest beer in town!!!

The service was horrible. When we got there there was only 3 tables that had customers. We had 3 waitresses just look at us. No "Hi, we will be right with you". We waited for 3 minutes just to be seated. The waitress spoke so quietly that we could not hear her. The waitress was so busy "flirting " with 1 customer she completely ignored her other 3 customers. The 2 other customers had to find another waitress to get a bill for the food. Our waitress was so engrossed with her male customer, that she even went as far as going out to the parking lot with him for a few minutes with him. We had to get her attention to get a bill. Then we had to go up to her again just so we could get a receipt. The food was good, service beyond lousy.

I came in here and wasn't feeling the greatest. I was just coming to get some food and Kaylee came up and was extremely nice. She had many customers and still was able to talk with everyone and get things done on time. She even came pass and said smile. Things always get better in seasons. Then to watch how she worked in her gifting was good. It actually boosted my mental because I felt overwhelmed but to see how gard she was working gave me drive. I needed this push today. Blessing
Best lunch experience ever. Toni was the best. I'll be back for lunch every time I'm in the area! This is my new favorite restaurant.

Bartender Symone was very inetentive. We were there fore 45 minutes and she only got us 1 single drink. She never acknowledged us one time after our initial order. Once we put our card down to pay, she grabbed it within 5 seconds of it hitting the table. We went to go find a table to sit at to order food with a better experience and made a comment to the hostess letting her know about our service where we were then confirmed by Symone who was crying and explained that she was busy and did the best that she could. Her bar had 5 groups of people at most at it and there were quite a few empty chairs. We asked for a manager who came out and accused us of not understanding and that they were doing no wrong. He was very rude and not customer friendly. The atmosphere they create here is one similar to high school. Where gossip is the number one priority. The managers act as if they are never in the wrong and that the customers bad experience was just a fluke. They do not take criticism very well and make the customers feel as if their opinion does not matter. Overall, i would not recommend this restraun to anyone who wants a friendly environment with an attentive staff.

Myself and 3 friends stopped in after spending the day looking at tux's for one of their weddings. Not many people and a good place for beer... usually... this experience was awful, took us about 15 minutes to get seated, 20 minutes to get our first round of beers, 40 minutes for the appetizers, another 30 minutes before the waitress even came by to ask us if we wanted a main course. We finally ordered, got the food, ate, and after the waitress came by and said she'd be right back we waited 25 minutes before asking the manager if we could finally get our tickets. By far the absolute worst experience at a restaurant we've had. Wouldn't recommend this location to a friend.

If you are expecting to talk to the bar tenders then good luck. It's just your typical bar with expensive drinks! Don't waste your time if you want a conversation with anyone working, even if they aren't busy it really isn't worth it. You can get a better conversation with your loca
l liquor store attendant. Worked in the bar serving area for years and all this place is and it's a trap. Don't waste your time or money. Thought I'd give it 3 tries before I posted, but it's the same every time. Just ok service and expensive drinks. Kinda sad because I've had much better service and conversations at other twin peaks restaurants. Too bad about this one.

Terrible service!  Dumb... Really dumb girls running around acting like servers!  Food is ok if you get to order it.  Our server LaShay was too busy hanging around at the front door by the fireplace laughing and chatting with other dumb girls!

Rude waitress food was not good don't come here the waitress said she was anti military cause I wore a marine sweatshirt and the waitress said I won't take pics cause of the USMC sweatshirt and said I don't support the military marines don't support this place

First and foremost our food was great and Thanks to Madison service was as well, but i felt so sorry for her that the manager felt our party of almost 25 people didn't deserve 2 waiters. Now we have been to Twin Peaks probably a hundred times since its opened and even with a party of 10 we have had 2 waiters. I even pulled the manager Mike to the side to ask could he make an executive decision to give her some help to ensure twin peaks service stays up to standards since i suggested the place for the party dinner. He looked at me and said no, I was shocked and also embarrassed at the same time for Twin Peaks to employ someone like that and I've always spoke highly of Twin Peaks. So thank you Madison for all you did for us all, and im sorry you under appreciated.

With chain restaurants, I write short reviews because basically they meet apparent corporate standards or they don't.

This breastaurant met all my expectations of a higher end chain. Been there three times. Friendly, cute servers and excellent food.

Twin peaks is a wonderful place!  I always enjoy their food and craft beer selection.   Of course, the beautiful ladies are also a nice addition to the experience!    Allie was a wonderful bartender and kept me and my friends entertained with jokes and conversation.    The atmosphere at twin peaks is wonderful and inviting to the customer.   If I did not travel for work every other week, I would be at twin peaks on a regular basis.   Great restaurant with great food!
The service is impeccable & the lady's are Gorgeous... Great job with the training too Morgan is doing great

I came into twin peaks with my friend to have a few beers. We sat at main bar with Kaylee and Sammie. They were very attentive to our needs and answered all our questions. I highly recommend the smoked wings tossed in the spicy Thai sauce.

Great place to grab a bite. Food was great, service was awesome and beer was super cold! Miranda from hogwarts took great care of us. We where super excited to find out they had dart boards and pool tables at this location.  We will be back next year when we come back into town.

Went in with a very large party.  Paid an entry fee for nothing.  Was not seated and was refused refund after sub-5min in the restaurant.  You'd figure a place would care about potential customers.  This particular location does not, which is unfortunate.  Our party rewarded another restaurant that wanted the business of 20+ people.
Gia the Trainee was off the charts amazing. One of the kindest people I've met in a while! Will definitely be returning to the business thanks to her awesome attitude!

I always enjoy going to Twin Peaks, and this is a nice one. There were lots of televisions and my wife joined me this time (so I didn't feel bad). 

My spicy chicken was awesome, and I felt like it was kind of healthy. The scenic views were nice, but we were actually there to watch football. Our server was friendly and the food came fast. She made the dessert with . I'll go back.

Twin Peaks in located in Castleton right by I-69 on 82nd Street. Parking is free with a large parking lot in front of the restaurant. 

Everything appeared handicapped accessible from the parking lot, entrance, restaurant, restrooms and the firepit on the patio.

We were seated immediately on the patio as requested at a tall-top table. The view was the parking lot but it was still nice to sit outdoors. We were just a few feet from the community fire pit where several folks were hanging out having a few beers.

Twin Peaks has daily drink specials from drafts to shots with $5 Happy Hour Bites and Drinks. They serve 29 degree beers if you enjoy ice cold beers. Many drink specials so check out the online menu. The restaurant is a great location for a meal, watch a game whether football, basketball or a fight but especially the upcoming Olympics. TV's are located everywhere and there is a pool table, a man cave and games.

The menu offers all your typical Pub food plus more. Several types of Pub Fries are available (recommend Hickory Smoke Pulled Pork or Brisket Chili), Wings, Fried Pickles plus more. A lunch menu is offered Monday -  Friday from 11:00 - 3:00pm. Burgers, tacos, ribs, salmon, pot roast, chicken are also on the menu.

Our food was good, the server brought our appetizers well before our dinner and she checked on us several times. We had a great time on the patio and will return.

This was our first time at Twin Peaks. We were visiting from Chicago and we've heard a lot about this restaurant. Don't be scared away by the parking lot...they have plenty of seating even if the parking lot appears to be full. We were greeted by a group of excited girls at the door. They were able to seat us right away. We wanted to watch a football game that was not the colts. The manager came over right away and asked which tv would be best for our table. 

We ordered an appetizer, sandwiches, and burgers. The food is reasonably priced and comes in large portions. The bloody Mary's are awesome!!...but the price is a little high at $8.75. 

They have a great patio with a ton of TVs. This will be great place to hang out in the summer. The garage doors open up to the restaurant. 

The service was ok but not the best. We would go back for the drinks and to watch a game. Overall...good restaurant with a great view!
Jessica P is the best waitress. She is fun and exciting and cute. If I ever come back I will definitely ask for her! Food was good. It was crowded but still great service.

To be honest, behind the ladies and breast restaurant theme,  there is decent food.  They do good burgers, apps, and down home entrees.  Being a beer snob, i hate that serve craft beer at 29 degrees, but overall,  it's a decent place. I would gladly go back with friends

Food is great. But, the service is not that great.  I went here two different times in 2 weeks.
One  time I met a group here and the other time by myself. 
Each time our food or mine came out. It took bar tenders 10 min to ask how the food was.  After you are done with the meal. They didn't ask if you wanted anything else. 
No interaction with new customers. Unless you are regular customer. They just talk away with them.

When you first walk in, your greeted immediately and with a smile.  Our waitress was amazing and always ask for Jaime.  The food was amazing, I had the haddock tacos and i highly recommend them. The service was out of this world right along with the food.

Great food great booze and even better customer service 5 stars 
1 draw back, a 1 star for manager Paul, unprofessional act of management and unlawful use of power in front of customers!!!! And we will not stand for it completely unacceptable behavior with the staff!

It is what it is. The service and food are not bad. Average bar food and drink prices. The place offers lots of seating and has several TV's for watching games and fights. We went there to watch the UFC Fights and had a fun time.

I forgot how much I love going to Twin Peaks, Lucy was my waitress and had a great attitude, they food is really good, plenty of TVs with a variety of things to watch, plenty of cold beer, there 13oz ribeye steak is amazing and I will definitely be coming there again soon! Everyone is friendly there! Definitely a fun place to go! I really recommend it and thank you Lucy for taking a selfie with me!
Hair in food, old tasted buffalo wings, a boob popped out and dipped in my chip dip...appetite lost
This was THE best Twin Peaks I've ever been to. But without the nan cave nor the fire pit, it's not the same. Sigh. Disappointed.
No need to make a reservation any day of the week. Convenient and quick seating. Cold beer and good food. Our server Ajna was great! Always willing to go back.

Came back to visit before a hockey game. Smoked wings with dry rub were very good. Chicken quesadilla good... Beer very cold. Service was a little slow but it's a big place. The parking lot can be full out front yet still lots of seating inside.

Had a great time stopping by twin peaks last night, the beer was EXTREMELY cold and frosted up the glass . I ended up ordering the chipotle chicken and meal come out PIPING hot,  just how I like it!!   

I sat at the bar with Kelsie and Brittany, both were attentive and on top of their game. Each had a VIBRANT smile that radiated across the room like an evening sunset on top of a beautiful mountain. 

The GM, Ryan is what I think his name was stopped by and made sure the service and food was up to my liking.  Then we proceeded to chat about the good ole days playing sports and acknowledging how the old body just doesn't up hold up like it used to. 

Thanks TP

I know with this kind of place, they are overly nice for good tips. Regardless, all the wait staff is friendly, food is good. Fairly priced. Their signature beers, the dirty blonde and knotty brunette are really good. So many tv's, you won't miss any sport you want to watch. I've only been there a few times, but had really good service. Better than Hooters and Tilted Kilt. Melanie and McKenzie were so far my favorite waitresses. I recommend to anyone who just wants to relax and have good food and drinks.

The beer is great! Very cold and great flavors. I had chicken and waffles and was very good. Prices are a little above average. Waitress was friendly and the service was good. Great place to watch sports endless TV's.

If I were to describe twin peaks to someone, I would tell them it is an upscale Hooters.  The main difference between Hooters and twin peaks is the quality and the customer service. I'm not saying hooters is bad and does not have good service, but I would pick twin peaks over hooters any day of the week.   Yes, the waitresses are dressed in cow girl attire and sometimes in skimpy lingerie, which makes coming to twin peaks even more enjoyable for a guy like me, but the food is terrific and the selection of craft beer on tap also makes it more reasonable to come to twin peaks.  The TVs all around the restaurant are a great feature if you want to watch a particular game or event for the day.  My friends and I like the $2 PBR beer special they have going on every day since it allows us to save money and enjoy beer at the same time.  The wings are awesome and I've enjoyed the avocado smash burger very much!!  You will not find a food item or a beer that you will not enjoy at twin peaks!  It is priceless!

Loved this place. Would have been a five but I'm EXTREMELY disappointed they've gutted the man cave by removing the couches and the pool tables. They didn't even have the firepit lit when I was there on 12/12. Sad to see a good place go downhill.

This place Bl**s. I am customer experience centric and this place doesn't get it. Pay a cover charge and not find a table. Go to a table and told you need to go back to the hostess station and make a reservation. Wait! I just paid $5 cover charge for no place to sit and eat. Then when I go to leave I tell Mr. Big Shot at the table where they are extorting money for entrance. Mr. Big Shot tells me the cover charge doesn't guarantee a seat. WHAT! I'll NEVER go back to this dump. I'll never recommend this dump. Give me a good experience in a dump and and I'm good. A bad experience in a dump ? NO WAY. 

Get your reality readjusted, Twin Peaks. There are better places for food etc. unless you rate food according to breast exposure. I'll be back in Indy fir business but I'll never be back here.

I would like to give this place 3.5 stars but we all know that's not possible.  My wife and I were out and had heard a lot about this place and decided to give it a try.

When we entered we noticed that my wife was the only girl in the establishment that wasn't working.  No big deal.  Our hostess turned out to be our waitress and was with us immediately.  She took our drink order and came back quickly with our waters and shortly thereafter with our cocktails.  We decided to order the pretzel and asked if they were large or small (they sell them in 1 or 2 pretzel options).  She said they weren't large so we ordered two.  When they arrived we were surprised at how large they were.  She offered to change it to one pretzel, but it wasn't a big deal so we kept them both.

We both ordered a variation of the philly chese steak sandwich.  I guess I shouldn't have expected much, but the steak was heavily seasoned with pepper and not the most tender meat I've ever had.  We also ordered bbq sauces and buffalo sauces on the side.  I was a bit surprised that they charged us $.50 per sauce.

The waitress was with us constantly, but not too much.  I would probably try this place again, but more likely with buddies as opposed to my wife.  Not a bad place.

If you can get past the uniforms, this place has GREAT food, cold beer and awesome service. Seems like what we all want in a restaurant, isn't it?  Try it 

We just keep coming back
Thanks so much for the birthday meal!!!  Lauren took such good care of us! And so nice that waitresses remember us and come over to say hi. Makes us feel special. Good job Sam.

The place is fun but the food is just okay. Definitely just more so bar food. We've had multiple different things there and I really wouldn't say there's anything that I go back for but the environment is a good time.

The food for the most part is really good. The beer is very cold and the bloody Mary's are the best around. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable of their restaurants menu. 

Unfortunately several times after being seated the waitresses are slow to even take a drink order. When I come in without friends the hostess looks irritated I don't want to sit at the bar. 

I'll still patronize Twin Peaks. Great seating and there is always something on the TV.  Plus the Bloody Marys.
Had really good food and adult drinks! Our waitress wasn't the nicest. Since we are in a pandemic they had to break our friend group up and do 3 and 3 at a table!

Not only is the beer kept below freezing, but the food is fiiire. Staff were sweet and absolutely gorgeous! My first time going but my husband went all the time in  Michigan. He got the chicken tenders and I got the Philly. Would definitely recommend and will go back soon!

We were very disappointed. Our server was clueless, rude and lazy. She was much more interested in a table of 2 guys next to our table. So much so that she sat with them more than once for 10 or so minutes at a time while we were there. The TV's looked like they had a bad streaming connection rather than satellite. We asked if there was something wrong or that could be done they said ,"oh, sure!" And nothing happened. They "couldn't find" any red wine when we asked for a glass after waiting 20 minutes on that response.  We literally bused our own table to an adjacent one because when we mentioned that we were done with our meals she asked if we wanted dessert!  The food was at best average. No reason to go back.

Food was average.  Beer selection decent.  Service above average.  Beer was definitely cold....love that.  Probably try the wings next time, Nashville chicken sandwich was more like a buffalo chicken sandwich.

Lots of TV for watching games, etc.

Been a usual to this place for about 4 years now and I believe that customer service is not getting any better.

A couple of weeks ago I took my dad so he would know a different place for beer and wings and it was a little disappointing.

I love the ambiance of this place, the design and decoration but if you don't get seated at the bar or the big tables you won't get the attention you deserve.

So, it was just the two of us but we were not asked to be seated at any of the two bars and instead taken to the low tables at the right wing of the restaurant where I could tell families were placed.

I'm not a restaurant manager and I know organization is a big part of this but if you're a customer and waitresses are wandering around and you can't find yours if you ask the first you see for hot sauce or the check the least you expect is being told that she is not taking care of that table and wait.

Anyway, boneless were good, and tasty, too bad summer shandy was not available but we liked our food.
this place is trash. takes forever to even get acknowledged and the service is insanely slow

I would like to start off by saying the food and service were decent (3 stars)

Now on to the terrible experience. We had a group of 10 people who came to watch the Stanley cup finals. We all ate and drank for the first two periods of the game. Just before the third period we were told a ufc event was about to be televised and we needed to pay "the cover" for said event. We told them we were here to watch the Stanley cup finals and not the ufc. We were told we had to pay "the cover" or leave despite the large amount of money we had already spent. We cashed out and went elsewhere to watch the game. Last time I will attempt to watch a game here.

Isabelle or Isabella, I lost my receipt, was our server. She had excellent recommendations and even guessed what we were searching for in the menu. I was between the philly and one of their signature burgers. She said the philly was her favorite and you got more food for 2$ less than what I was looking at. The fries were awesome as well. I've never been to philly but heard the bun should be moist/wet from the meet and fixings and it was which I love.

Is it possible to give this a zero?  It is a terrible experience from the front door.  Food, drinks, rude wait staff. I couldn't believe that there were children allowed here!   Some of the Wait staff was nice but also paid to be nice and trying to get big tips. 
Go somewhere else - or at least to a strip club if that what you are looking for...

Heard that they had really good food and obviously expected a huge male population however I downed 4 waters and I was still so thirsty because the food was so salty. 

We had three servers in a 3 hour period. Our first waitress was nice but informed us she was finishing her shift and that we could transfer or close tab. To benefit her getting tips, we closed. However we were here for the game and it was clearly not even halftime. So we went without a waitress for 30-40 mins. Finally, we flagged down one and she was very good while we had her but so busy that we were left unattended to several times. 

Everyone got wings for the most part and I have several that had broken bones and dark meat. The beer was probably the highlight of the whole experience. Served at 29 degrees. Tasted great ice cold.

My one and only time in there sucked. First off, I was annoyed with the lack of beer knowledge by the bartender who recommended Coors since it's her favorite beer at college *eyeroll* when I ordered one of their signature beers(which are subpar btw) I was asked if I want a " man size" or a "little girl size" beer(obviously something corporate tells them to say because I heard another bartender say it too). Wow! How sexist! I can drink most men under the table so screw you basically. ...ordered the "buffalo chili burger" I asked if it was actually buffalo meat, she said yes so I ordered it cooked medium so it wouldn't be so tough. It came out cold, well done and stiff as a hockey puck. I sent it back. ..30min later it came out hot and well done like a hockey puck. Management came over and informed me it wouldn't be cooked Medium because they are in fact PRECOOKED beef patties that are topped with 'buffalo chili'. Wow. So I didn't get to eat anything and was so frustrated I had to wait an hour total just to be informed of that.  So I won't be back.  Too bad because the bones of the place very much remind me of the old Loon Lake and they have a very nice patio.

I popped in her because I had to drop my car off next door for service.    I didn't order any food so take this review with a grain of salt.

I went straight to the bar and was immediately greeted by a friendly bartender.  The beer special on this day was excellent ($2.90 tall Miller Lites on Wednesdays) so no complaint there.

I ne er had a chance to visit this space in its previous life (as a wild game-themed restaurant) so I don't know what ki d of renovations have been made.   However, from what I saw, it is a pretty neat building.   All alpine-themed to go with the name. 

The bar crowd was pretty chill.  It was primarily (male) professionals having a cold one after work.

Next  time I come here I'll have to try the  wings as there is a separate wing menu (a sign that they're good).

This has been my 2nd time here. The first time was for the Mike Tyson fight.  The waitresses are very nice, and the food comes out very quickly.  Yesterday when I went I noticed alot of families are there to eat. There are a ton of TV's with different sporting games being played. If you order an appetizer wait a minute to order your meal because the food comes out that fast.  I like to take my time eating my appetizer.  
The food so yesterday I got the loaded potato soup and it was so, so good. I asked for green onions on the side to add to my soup.  That soup was so good not salty at all.  It had fresh bacon, potatoes and cheese.  
We also order fried pickles which was enough pickles to feed 4 people.  It comes with ranch,  and they were not greasy at all.  They were a mild flavor pickle so not tart.  I had the cheeseburger and added bacon for .99 cents.  The bacon is a nice thick cut of bacon.  The burger comes with lettuce,  tomato,  grilled onions, and mustard. The bun did break apart on the bottom for some reason. The patty is a thick piece of meat and it was very good.  
I will definitely go back I would like to try their Cuban sandwich.  I was going to get it but she said it's on a hoagie bun.  I would like to see if they can do that sandwich on their Texas toast they serve with the soup.  
Lastly,  I would like to see this restaurant have the tables/ bar top table more spread.  It's like part of the restaurant is social distancing and part of it is not. They are located in Marion County so the capacity should be less according to the Governor rules.  The restaurant both times has been packed with every table filled.  People do wear there mask to the bathroom,  and around the restaurant.  When seated our table was not clean so I asked to sit some where else.  I will definitely go back,  but would like to see either less people or the covid cases be less.

Twin Peaks is your typical guys bar, way above Hooters, and on par with tilted kilt.  The thing that puts it over the top is the ICE cold beer served at 29 degrees.  Servers are attentive and knowledgeable about the menu.  Jade is a true sports fan, we chatted about the World Series and she quoted stats about both the Dodgers and the Astros

If you never wondered into a Twin Peaks it will not take you long to figure the tongue-in-cheek name.  Twin Peaks is to the rugged northwest what Hooters  is to sunny Florida.  With that out of the way it's the food that keeps us coming back (don't believe me?  Ask the wife this last stop was her call). This time it was the fried pork rind appetizer (served with a Nashville hot sauce ) that pulled us in, last time it was the smoke wings and chili, & the time before that the pulled pork sandwich (my daughter's favorite).  The portions are hearty, the flavor delivers on every dish, and the fries are always golden & crunchy.  Finally, I cannot write a review without mentioning that the draft beers always show up with a beer ice berg, that only occurs when the mugs and beers are perfectly chilled !

I hate to leave bad reviews... I believe in giving the benefit of a doubt, but I have to review with honesty. The atmosphere is cool.. Really cold beer.. AWESOME!!! TV's at the urinal... Burger was good. Now comes the bad part.. Two of the party had order screwed up. The food came to the table piece meal and not at once or even close to being within five minutes of each other.. Come on ... It's freaking burgers, fries and run of the mill bar food. To have 10 minutes lapse between orders arriving.. Jeez!! Had to ask for refills of beer, sodas... Then you waited for 10 minutes for the refills!! All in all... Fair food, nice atmosphere, my feminist daughters were appalled by the Hooter esque dressed waitresses, crappy service... Two stars!

Not one of the phone numbers listed on the website or on Yelp work for this restaurant.  The website to order food to go doesn't work. Dont list it as an option if you dont intend to use it or make it available.
Great food for a good place and the house blonde was fantastic. Any place with asparagus is a great place. Alyssa and Bree were both wonderful and attentive.

I received very good customer service so that made my experience better. Their tenderloins are strange. They're not like us Hoosiers are used to. The breading is too thick and they slap a slice of american cheese on it. It just wasnt what we would think of as a tenderloin. I took a few bites and boxed it. I thought that if I took it home I could doctor it up somehow. It was gross. 

I've had other meals here that were pretty food. I think they should personally take the tenderloin off the menu if they're not going to do it right. I have never had a bad tenderloin. I didnt even think it was possible.

Horrible. I go out to eat quite a bit and this was one of the worst experiences I've had overall. The wait to order drinks, order food, get food, all of it was a very long time. And they weren't packed, just generally busy. We are talking 15 mins to order drinks. Then after that I got my meal finally. I ordered the pot roast. There is usually some fat in the meat- that is to be expected. There was only 4 bites of meat. The rest was fat. I'm going to have to go get something else to eat after this because I don't want to eat $15 slimy fat.

Nice arrangement of TV's, but the food and drink prices are more than I would like to pay. Take away their hook and it's a run of the mill joint.

The bartenders aren't interested in talking to you, if that's what you're wondering.
Food = tasty and quickly prepared.  Beverages = good beer selection, large pours.  Interior = clean and very open (great sight lines).  Staff = pleasant, helpful and nice to observe (as expected).

Our server Toni was AWESOME! She did a great job recommending different items from the menu and was also super personable. I would highly recommended Twin Peaks on 82nd Street but even more so, request Toni! Wonderful service!

The waitresses are usually great. But management is not. They cater only to white customers. You hear nothing but country music and rock and roll. There are times when there are literally 65-70% black and Latino customers and all you hear is music that caters to whites. There have slowly added women of color to the team of waitresses but they don't seem to stick around very long. One night, my friends and I came in for fight night and the place was jammed packed. They took our money at the door and there were no seats available for us to sit in. So we had to stand and hope that four people would leave so that we could be seated. Managers were rude when we asked about it. Probably because there were cops with them that were working in the building that night which is not surprising. We finally spot a table of four leaving and then four guys that had just walked in the building and who just so happened to be white men hurried up and sat at that table and we told them that we were there before they were and management told us that they were there before we were. We knew this wasn't true but it put us all in a potentially bad situation. We are not trouble makers but we were very angry. Especially since all they had to do is write down names at the door and keep track of tables. We saw a waitress arguing with another group of black men for the same reason at the same time and they told us the same thing had happened to them.
